  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7087 trading below the GEX flip at 7096, dealers are in negative gamma territory and likely buying this 1.6% dip to hedge short gamma positions, providing support around current levels. The massive positive gamma wall at 7100 (+4913.5M) should act as strong magnetic resistance, while the negative gamma pocket at 7040 (-902M) represents the key downside level where dealer buying accelerates. Expect mean-reverting price action with dealers selling any bounce toward 7100-7150 and buying weakness toward 7040.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect a bounce back toward 7100 with limited downside past 7040.",
